Multinomial logistic regression

The mllogreg.py is the main file. To run the code with default parameters type the following:

>>python mllogreg.py 

If you type:

>> python mllogreg.py -gc

Then you will run gradient check


If you type:

>> python mllogreg.py -h

You will get the list of the possible parameters


Additional work:

If you can run L-BFGS-B algorithm from scipy.optimize
For example:
>> python mllogreg.py -md l_bfgs_b -bs 50000 -n 1 


Training stops if the validation error increases 10 times in succession
Plots show errors after each epoch


Required dependencies:
1. Python 2.7.3
2. Numpy
3. Scipy
4. Matplotlib

